library(sf)
library(tidyverse)
library(ggspatial)
library(ggthemes)
library(raster)
neighborhoods <- st_read("neighborhoods.kml")

##   `/Users/Noah 1/Documents/GSD/Software Portfolio/Assignment-1/neighborhoods.kml' 
##   using driver `KML'
## Simple feature collection with 13 features and 2 fields
## Geometry type: POLYGON
## Dimension:     XY
## Bounding box:  xmin: -71.1604 ymin: 42.35253 xmax: -71.06404 ymax: 42.40376
## Geodetic CRS:  WGS 84
parks <- st_read("recreation.kml")
## Reading layer `recreation' from data source 
##   `/Users/Noah 1/Documents/GSD/Software Portfolio/Assignment-1/recreation.kml' 
##   using driver `KML'
## Simple feature collection with 249 features and 2 fields
## Geometry type: MULTIPOLYGON
## Dimension:     XY
## Bounding box:  xmin: -71.15971 ymin: 42.35298 xmax: -71.06624 ymax: 42.40435
## Geodetic CRS:  WGS 84
playgrounds <- st_read("playgrounds.geojson")
## Reading layer `playgrounds' from data source 
##   `/Users/Noah 1/Documents/GSD/Software Portfolio/Assignment-1/playgrounds.geojson' 
##   using driver `GeoJSON'
## Simple feature collection with 58 features and 2 fields
## Geometry type: POINT
## Dimension:     XY
## Bounding box:  xmin: -71.1553 ymin: 42.35472 xmax: -71.06878 ymax: 42.3998
## Geodetic CRS:  WGS 84
assignment_one <- ggplot() +
  annotation_map_tile(zoomin = 0, progress = "none", type = "cartolight") +
  geom_sf(data = neighborhoods, color = "gray", alpha = 0.05, size = 0.5) +
  geom_sf(data = parks, fill = "green", alpha = 0.5, size = 0) +
  geom_sf(data = playgrounds, shape = 16, color = "darkviolet", aes(color = "playgrounds")) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = "green", name = "") +
  scale_color_manual(values = "darkviolet", name = "") +
  labs(caption = "Map generated by Noah Levine, map tiles by Stamen Design, and data by OpenStreetMap.") +
  theme_map()

assignment_one
